14 SECTION 9. ORS 811.050 is amended to read:
15 811.050. (1) A person commits the offense of failure of a motor vehicle operator to yield to a
16 rider on a bicycle lane if the person is operating a motor vehicle and the person does not yield the
17 right of way to a person operating a bicycle, electric assisted bicycle, electric personal assistive
18 mobility device, moped, motor assisted scooter, powered micromobility device or motorized
19 wheelchair upon a bicycle lane.
20 (2) This section does not require a person operating a moped to yield the right of way to a bi-
21 cycle or a motor assisted scooter if the moped is operated on a bicycle lane in the manner permitted
22 under ORS 811.440.
23 (3) The offense described in this section, failure of a motor vehicle operator to yield to a rider
24 on a bicycle lane, is a Class B traffic violation.
