1 (4) Is equipped with a power source that is incapable of propelling the vehicle at a speed of
2 greater than [24] 20 miles per hour on level ground and:
3 (a) If the power source is a combustion engine, has a piston or rotor displacement of 35 cubic
4 centimeters or less regardless of the number of chambers in the power source; or
5 (b) If the power source is electric, has a power output of not more than 1,000 watts.
6 SECTION 12. ORS 814.512 is amended to read:
7 814.512. (1) A person operating a motor assisted scooter commits the offense of unlawful opera-
8 tion of a motor assisted scooter if:
9 (a) The person is under [16] 14 years of age; or
10 (b) The person operates a motor assisted scooter at a rate of speed exceeding [15] 20 miles per
11 hour.
12 (2) The offense described in this section, unlawful operation of a motor assisted scooter, is a
13 Class D traffic violation.
