10 SECTION 22. ORS 153.633 is amended to read:
11 153.633. (1) In any criminal action in a circuit court in which a fine is imposed, the lesser of the
12 following amounts is payable to the state before any other distribution of the fine is made:
13 (a) $65; or
14 (b) The amount of the fine if the fine is less than $65.
15 (2) In any criminal action in a justice or municipal court in which a fine is imposed, the lesser
16 of the following amounts is payable to the state before any other distribution of the fine is made:
17 (a) $50; or
18 (b) The amount of the fine if the fine is less than $50.
19 (3) A justice or municipal court shall forward the amount prescribed under subsection (2) of this
20 section to the Department of Revenue for deposit in the Criminal Fine Account.
21 (4)(a) The provisions of this section do not apply to fines imposed under ORS 339.990.
22 (b) The provisions of subsection (2) of this section do not apply to fines imposed in justice and
23 municipal courts under ORS 811.590, [814.485,] 814.486, [814.534,] 814.536[, 814.600] or 830.990 (1).
24 SECTION 23. ORS 153.645 is amended to read:
